explanation: The solution uses a sliding window approach with two pointers (l and r) to efficiently traverse the string s. It maintains a map to track the frequency of characters in t and another map to track the frequency of characters in the current window. The algorithm iterates through s, expanding the window to the right until all characters in t are present in the window. Then, it shrinks the window from the left while maintaining the condition that all characters in t are present. The minimum window length and its starting index are updated accordingly. This approach achieves O(m + n) time complexity because each character in s and t is visited at most twice. The space complexity is O(m) due to the windowCounts map, which can store up to m characters in the worst case.

